tweet_raw: I think many people especially in the XRP community are confused about DeFi what it is some even saying its a useless use case and offers nothing.Lets begin from the fact that DeFi is the core use case and fundamental value proposition of blockchain technology as a whole and the reason this whole thing started from Satoshi and later the XRPL creators that built the OG DeFi chain by introducting the first DEX tokenization features and more. DeFi is literally the #1 use case in crypto with the most TVL in the industry and crucial use cases such as decentralized exchanges borrowing/lending stablecoins derivatives and basically anything finance related. Sending and exchanging value P2P is basically the core DeFi function so its prerequisite for payments. And since AMMs have now been the standard DeFi use case and protocol for the past few years with the increased liquidity and volume the AMM will offer it also improves the payment use cases.And to people who are still confused DeFi is an open financial ecosystem of apps that run on top of blockchain technology. The goal is to replace middlemen in traditional financial systems with automation. DeFi refers to financial services and applications that are automated and trustless. Its the #1 use case and will always be. And for that reason XRPLs core use case and value proposition will always be DeFi too.

tweet_raw: Ill also give you a bit of cultural context here because I have lived in Uttarakhand for 10+ years. Once you leave the plains and head into the mountains we are a very safe community up here. There are hardly any incidents of petty thefts in buses or shared taxis or pickpocket cases etc. Mountain communities live on trust. You will often find people leaving bags in the bus when going for lunch or leaving bags next to a shop in a market etc. Everyone watches for each other and there is a feeling of trust. When I first moved here I found it deeply unsettling and it took a few years to get used to - trust.Kids who grow up here dont know how dog eat dog the outside world is. They almost always get caught out when they get pickpocketed or have their bags stolen. Its a rite of passage in learning about life in India for them.

tweet_raw: BIG UPDATE TIME @btcgreenhouse If you have been following me long enough you will know that myself and Adam from @coinoswallet have working on a dedicated bitcoin heated greenhouse. The goal is to provide food electricity and of course bitcoin. As a bonus education and a learning environment on all three.As of today this is where the project stands and what we need to accomplish before going live with fundraising.Because the project is happening on disputed territory only disputed by one side aka the Canadian Gov permission is required by the indigenous locals. On this front we have discussed and received the go ahead. The project was displayed at the local energy symposium to an overwhelmingly positive reception. Who knew that people want high quality organic food locally produced with bitcoin and electricity as a bonus without all the fiat bullshit!The next step is a concept and design for which we have engaged a company called Ceres (ceresgs.com/). They have agreed to take the project on and help us design and implement a bitcoin heated greenhouse. They are estimating a cost of $600kUSD for lockup aka fully finished with lock and key. They are asking for a $7K retainer to begin the engineering work on the heat recovery from the bitcoin mining.For the bitcoin mine we are looking at a 100KW setup from @upstreamdatainc with dry cooler and then pluming the hot loop into the floor of the greenhouse. We will be using @Whatsminer_MBT hydro cooled ASICs approximately 10 to begin. The site for the greenhouse is 1 hectare and the actual footprint will be around 9600 square feet. With the extra heat we are going to provide services to a mill which will positioned along side the greenhouse in the form of a kiln. Extra heat will be used as well for drying firewood for locals. IF we still have extra we will look to do something a la the bathhouse in New York (abathhouse.com/). This would be a bonus of course but we want to dream big. As for the design of the greenhouse you can see it pictured below. A central headhouse and 4 adjoining greenhouses each with an individual climate controlled environment so we can grow pretty much anything we like. The headhouse will be glass and have a solarized rooftop. The front side will be in the style of stained glass with the design provided by local indigenous artists. We can go for either ultimate cost savings and efficiency or something that is slightly more beautiful and of course we are going for the second option. In terms of what is grown we are collecting feedback from the community and further to that we will provide the github for the bitcoin community to provide feedback as well. Everything about this project will be open sourced that way it can be replicated and improved upon. If you listened to the interview about the project you will remember the discussion of the royalties and distribution of mined bitcoin. For this we are using @Liquid_BTC  to create an asset that when held in a wallet will receive bitcoin generated by the project. This will be in the form of mined bitcoin bitcoin purchased by power sales and revenue generated by selling the food produced inside the greenhouse. All income will be reinvested into the hardest money of all time. You can listen here: ungovernablemisfits.com/podcâ€¦The last remaining thing to do before we launch the crowd funding is come up with a name in the local language. This process requires local knowledge holders and will hopefully be ready in a few weeks. You might think coming up with a name is a simple thing however here a name can only be produced a certain way the right way. Once the name has been given we will go live with the website the @geyserfund as well as the github. We welcome feedback from the community and hope to engage the many brilliant minds that exist in #Bitcoin and elsewhere. tweet_text: the business model of some cryptocurrencies are based mostly on speculation hype trading and market making  some teams dont think about it all  some efforts at tokenomic design attempt to capitalize on game theory and network usage  but one of the most impressive aspects of polkadot 20 tokenomics is the inclusion of a thoughtful burn mechanism  this mechanism capitalizes on the technical design of polkadot which is to provide secure high quality efficient and flexible blockspace for projects to incorporate into their products  whether those products are apps chains smart contracts or more  they will need blockspace to scale and polkadot provides this service much like aws provides serverless compute and more for companies around the world   projects will pay dot for blockspace and as the demand for their products grow the more blockspace theyll need this dot will then be burned adding a second deflationary pressure to the token the first being an about 30 day periodic treasury burn  so it is in the interest of polkadot and its holders to promote and attract users to these products built on the network not to directly compete and put more dot on the market from the treasury if you want number go up  focus on optimizing within the design of the tokenomics  think bigger  do you agree disagree what do you think is best to promote polkadot let me know in the comments
tweet_raw: The business model of some cryptocurrencies are based mostly on speculation hype trading and market makingSome teams donâ€™t think about it allSome efforts at tokenomic design attempt to capitalize on game theory and network usageBut one of the most impressive aspects of @Polkadot 2.0 tokenomics is the inclusion of a thoughtful burn mechanismThis mechanism capitalizes on the technical design of Polkadot which is to provide secure high quality efficient and flexible blockspace for projects to incorporate into their productsWhether those products are apps chains smart contracts or more - they will need blockspace to scale. And Polkadot provides this service much like AWS provides serverless compute (and more) for companies around the world Projects will pay $DOT for blockspace and as the demand for their products grow the more blockspace theyâ€™ll need. This $DOT will then be burned adding a second deflationary pressure to the token. The first being an about 30 day periodic treasury burnSo it is in the interest of Polkadot and its holders to promote and attract users to these products built on the network. NOT to directly compete and put more $DOT on the market from the treasury. If you want number go up - focus on optimizing within the design of the tokenomicsThink biggerDo you agree? Disagree? What do you think is best to promote Polkadot? Let me know in the comments
